                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1121 Blodgett, Walton/168: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain (<persName type="from"
                            >Bowers</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-21T16:00:00+00:00"
                            >January 21, 1934—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 21—2:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. My telegram No. 10, January 20, 3 p.m.<note n="48" xml:id="d529fn48">Not
                        printed.</note> Upon receiving information this morning that … had been
                    reimprisoned last night immediately got in touch with the Foreign Minister who
                    states this action must have been taken not because of judgment but because of
                    what I am positive was a false accusation from Palma that they were planning
                    escape. Judgment which may be announced tomorrow will merely place accused at
                    disposition of the Court and will not according to the Foreign Office entail
                    reimprisonment. Minister of Foreign Affairs after our conversation talked with
                    Ministers of War and Justice and thereafter telephoned me that imperative orders
                    for release of prisoners from jail would <pb facs="0820" n="716" xml:id="pg_716"
                    /> be sent first thing tomorrow morning. He expects to phone me at noon tomorrow
                    that prisoners have been released.</p>
                <p>You may wish to inform press of exact situation so that Monday’s papers may carry
                    true story.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
